Doing something like 
{code:java}
AssertScalarsEqual(*col->GetScalar(2).ValueOrDie(), *ScalarFromJSON(type, R"(null)"));{code}
does not show up in Valgrind. So I think something should be wrong with the matcher.

Have narrowed it down to this:

Commenting out the below part in the line [here|https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/74f512260fa69903feac61e1287f6954a3d98204/cpp/src/arrow/testing/matchers.h#L204]:
{code:java}
testing::PrintToString(value){code}
gets rid of the two errors: UninitCondition and UinitValue.

Guessing PrintToString() doesn't play well with smart pointers, which are being passed to ResultWith via GetScalar?
